BREAKING: Greenock WILL bid to become a city despite reservations from residents. Councillors have agreed unanimously to go ahead with a bid.

The bid proposal says: "It [city status] can help to shine a light on an area which has been there for our country at important moments and has the ambition and drive to be there again and to take its place as a significant
Scottish and UK city." #ldreporter
Council chiefs have, however, set out a bid proposal which says city status can be a "catalyst" for additional jobs and investment and bringing extra visitors to the area

Results of a community survey showed 61 per cent of respondents would NOT back a bid for Greenock to become a city while 63 per cent said they didn't believe it would help to boost the population. 56 per cent don't believe city status would encourage investment

Inverclyde Council's policy and resources committee will  be meeting this afternoon with a key decision to be made on whether Greenock should bid for city status as part of the Platinum Jubilee celebrations.  #ldreporter
